	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Last month Red Bull Music Academy did a nearly-2-hour-long lecture/interview with Hirokazu &quot;Hip&quot; TANAKA where he discusses details of music-making, hardware engineering decisions (regarding the Gameboy and Famicom), the history of Nintendo of Japan, music genres, and all sorts of other stuff.  I figure folks would enjoy this:<br /><br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F7J5GlE3YLQ">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=F7J5GlE3YLQ</a><!-- m --><br /><br />English subtitles are available for the Japanese portions (click the &quot;CC&quot; button in the video).<br /><br />Main website reference: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.redbullmusicacademy.com/magazine/hip-tanaka-2014-lecture">http://www.redbullmusicacademy.com/maga ... 14-lecture</a><!-- m -->

		

		</td>
	</tr>
